    OUR SERVICES

    AND EXPERIENCE

    With 25+ years of experience and over 1 GW+ of solar and energy storage projects to date, Castillo Engineering is one of the most experienced solar and energy storage engineering firms in the United States. Castillo Engineering delivers expertise in full service (electrical, structural, medium & high voltage) solar and energy storage design, engineering, and consulting services for projects ranging from residential to utility-scale. From 5 kW to 500 MW, we utilize our proprietary site-specific design optimization process to reduce project costs, accelerate your installations & maximize project profitability - all while maintaining the highest quality.

    Live Technical & Customer Support

    +

    Our solar design expertise results in a minimum bill of materials, eliminating wastage and cost overruns that drain the profitability of your project, without compromising quality. As a result, you finish your projects faster, with less material and more profit.

    Due to the fact that our extensive customer base across the country utilizes a wide variety of products, alongside our strong manufacturer relationships that have been developed over the past 25+ years, we are always apprised of the latest products being introduced to the market. As a result, our engineers offer expert equipment selection recommendations to ensure that each product best suits your project needs, so that you permit quickly, install easily, and maximize project value.

    Every Castillo client has a dedicated Technical Support Engineer to assist you with any design changes, provide status updates, and expert – during construction – technical phone support so you can complete your projects on-time, under budget, and with the quality your clients’ demand. No more waiting for returned emails or phone calls. We get you the information and assistance you need when you need it most.
